rComments: This professor was very condescending and not easy to approach. She would make unnecessary comments about students who did not attend class and was often brash and unapproachable. She had a suggestion box for the first two classes and got rid of it when she got a suggestion she didn't like. I found the midterm unfair and a bad test of knowledge.

rComments: Lectures are almost impossible to keep up with. If you do your readings beforehand, you might catch a few points. The prof can be a bit childish at times. Lots of students just stopped coming to class, because lectures were useless. All I can say is if you want a good grade, keep up with your readings religiously and take down good notes from them.

Terrible professor, lectures were pointlessly long, we were always behind schedule despite having a three hour lecture. I was looking forward to this course because its first half was very interesting, but the professor ruined it for me. I wanted to drop it and take it over the summer, but guess what she's teaching that one too.

Worst prof I've ever had. Averages out Cs and Ds unless you're one of her favorites, and sit in the front to chat and compliment her. I actually felt sick after taking this class. Rude, monotonous, and brash to her students I wouldn't recommend this course to my worst enemy. It was, however a requirement (and the only reason people stay in).

Does not use slides or any visual aids but goes so quickly and lectures on so many things even native english speaking expressed difficulty following her pace, but still refuses to provide any visual aid assumes we knows a lot of stuff in the topic in this intro class and breezes through topics.  HEAVILY BASED ON READINGS  nice proff otherwise
